hwVdslQam.description: The MIB module defining objects for the management of a pair of VDSL modems at each end of the VDSL line. Each such line has an entry in an ifTable which may include multiple modem lines. An agent may reside at either end of the VDSL line however the MIB is designed to require no management communication between them beyond that inherent in the low-level VDSL line protocol. The agent may monitor and control this protocol for its needs. VDSL lines may support optional Fast or Interleaved channels. If these are supported, additional entries corresponding to the supported channels must be created in the ifTable. Thus a VDSL line that supports both channels will have three entries in the ifTable, one for each physical, fast, and interleaved, whose ifType values are equal to vdsl(97), fast(125), and interleaved(124), respectively. The ifStackTable is used to represent the relationship between the entries. Naming Conventions: Vtuc -- (VTUC) modem at near (Central) end of line Vtur -- (VTUR) modem at Remote end of line Vtu -- One of either Vtuc or Vtur Curr -- Current Prev -- Previous Atn -- Attenuation ES -- Errored Second. LCS -- Line Code Specific Lof -- Loss of Frame Lol -- Loss of Link Los -- Loss of Signal Lpr -- Loss of Power xxxs -- interval of Seconds in which xxx occurs (e.g., xxx=Lof, Los, Lpr) Max -- Maximum Mgn -- Margin Min -- Minimum Psd -- Power Spectral Density Snr -- Signal to Noise Ratio Tx -- Transmit Blks -- Blocks, a data unit, see vdslVtuXChanCrcBlockLength

VdslLineCodingType.name: VdslLineCodingType
VdslLineCodingType.description: This data type is used as the syntax for the VDSL Line Code.

VdslLineEntity.name: VdslLineEntity
VdslLineEntity.description: Identifies a modem as being either Vtuc or Vtur. A VDSL line consists of two modems, a Vtuc and a Vtur.

vdslLineTable.name: vdslLineTable
vdslLineTable.description: This table includes common attributes describing both ends of the line. It is required for all VDSL physical interfaces. VDSL physical interfaces are those ifEntries where ifType is equal to vdsl(97).

vdslLineCoding.name: vdslLineCoding
vdslLineCoding.description: Specifies the VDSL coding type used on this line.

vdslLineType.name: vdslLineType
vdslLineType.description: Defines the type of VDSL physical line entity that exists, by defining whether and how the line is channelized. If the line is channelized, the value will be other than noChannel(1). This object defines which channel type(s) are supported. In the case that the line is channelized, the manager can use the ifStackTable to determine the ifIndex for the associated channel(s).

vdslLineConfProfile.name: vdslLineConfProfile
vdslLineConfProfile.description: The value of this object identifies the row in the VDSL Line Configuration Profile Table, ( vdslLineConfProfileTable ), which applies for this VDSL line, and channels if applicable.

vdslLineAlarmConfProfile.name: vdslLineAlarmConfProfile
vdslLineAlarmConfProfile.description: The value of this object identifies the row in the VDSL Line Alarm Configuration Profile Table, ( vdslLineAlarmConfProfileTable ), which applies to this VDSL line, and channels if applicable.

vdslPhysTable.name: vdslPhysTable
vdslPhysTable.description: This table provides one row for each Vtu. Each row contains the Physical Layer Parameters table for that Vtu. VDSL physical interfaces are those ifEntries where ifType is equal to vdsl(97).

vdslPhysSide.name: vdslPhysSide
vdslPhysSide.description: Identifies whether the modem is the Vtuc or Vtur.

vdslInvSerialNumber.name: vdslInvSerialNumber
vdslInvSerialNumber.description: The vendor specific string that identifies the vendor equipment.

vdslInvVendorID.name: vdslInvVendorID
vdslInvVendorID.description: The vendor ID code is a copy of the binary vendor identification field defined by the PHY[10] and expressed as readable characters.

vdslInvVersionNumber.name: vdslInvVersionNumber
vdslInvVersionNumber.description: The vendor specific version number sent by this Vtu as part of the initialization messages. It is a copy of the binary version number field defined by the PHY[10] and expressed as readable characters.

vdslCurrSnrMgn.name: vdslCurrSnrMgn
vdslCurrSnrMgn.description: Noise Margin as seen by this Vtu with respect to its received signal in tenth dB.

vdslCurrAtn.name: vdslCurrAtn
vdslCurrAtn.description: Measured difference in the total power transmitted by the peer Vtu and the total power received by this Vtu.

hwVdslActualRate.name: hwVdslActualRate
hwVdslActualRate.description: The actual rate of this Vtu.

vdslCurrStatus.name: vdslCurrStatus
vdslCurrStatus.description: Indicates current state of the Vtu line. This is a bit-map of possible conditions. The various bit positions are: 0 noDefect There no defects on the line 1 lossOfFraming Vtu failure due to not receiving valid frame. 2 lossOfSignal Vtu failure due to not receiving signal. 3 lossOfPower Vtu failure due to loss of power. 4 lossOfSignalQuality Loss of Signal Quality is declared when the Noise Margin falls below the Minimum Noise Margin, or the bit-error-rate exceeds 10^-7. 5 lossOfLink Vtu failure due to inability to link with peer Vtu. 6 dataInitFailure Vtu failure during initialization due to bit errors corrupting startup exchange data. 7 configInitFailure Vtu failure during initialization due to peer Vtu not able to support requested configuration. 8 protocolInitFailure Vtu failure during initialization due to incompatible protocol used by the peer Vtu. 9 noPeerVtuPresent Vtu failure during initialization due to no activation sequence detected from peer Vtu. This is intended to supplement ifOperStatus.

vdslCurrOutputPwr.name: vdslCurrOutputPwr
vdslCurrOutputPwr.description: Measured total output power transmitted by this ATU. This is the measurement that was reported during the last activation sequence.

vdslCurrAttainableRate.name: vdslCurrAttainableRate
vdslCurrAttainableRate.description: Indicates the maximum currently attainable data rate by the Vtu. This value will be equal or greater than the current line rate.

vdslChanTable.name: vdslChanTable
vdslChanTable.description: This table provides one row for each Vtu channel. VDSL channel interfaces are those ifEntries where ifType is equal to interleave(124) or fast(125).

vdslChanInterleaveDelay.name: vdslChanInterleaveDelay
vdslChanInterleaveDelay.description: Interleave Delay for this channel. Interleave delay applies only to the interleave (slow) channel and defines the mapping (relative spacing) between subsequent input bytes at the interleaver input and their placement in the bit stream at the interleaver output. Larger numbers provide greater separation between consecutive input bytes in the output bit stream allowing for improved impulse noise immunity at the expense of payload latency. In the case where the ifType is fast(125), use noSuchObject.

vdslChanCrcBlockLength.name: vdslChanCrcBlockLength
vdslChanCrcBlockLength.description: Indicates the length of the channel data-block on which the CRC operates.

vdslPerfDataTable.name: vdslPerfDataTable
vdslPerfDataTable.description: This table provides one row for each VDSL physical interface. VDSL physical interfaces are those ifEntries where ifType is equal to vdsl(97).

vdslPerfValidIntervals.name: vdslPerfValidIntervals
vdslPerfValidIntervals.description: Valid Intervals per xxxValidInterval definition found in HC-PerfHist-TC-MIB.

vdslPerfInvalidIntervals.name: vdslPerfInvalidIntervals
vdslPerfInvalidIntervals.description: Invalid Intervals per xxxInvalidInterval definition found in HC-PerfHist-TC-MIB.

vdslPerfLofs.name: vdslPerfLofs
vdslPerfLofs.description: Count of seconds since the unit was last reset that there was Loss of Framing.

vdslPerfLoss.name: vdslPerfLoss
vdslPerfLoss.description: Count of seconds since the unit was last reset that there was Loss of Signal.

vdslPerfLprs.name: vdslPerfLprs
vdslPerfLprs.description: Count of seconds since the unit was last reset that there was Loss of Power.

vdslPerfESs.name: vdslPerfESs
vdslPerfESs.description: Count of Errored Seconds since the unit was last reset. An Errored Second is a one-second interval containing one or more crc anomalies, or one or more los defects.

vdslPerfInits.name: vdslPerfInits
vdslPerfInits.description: Count of the line initialization attempts since the unit was last reset. This count includes both successful and failed attempts.

vdslPerfCurr15MinTimeElapsed.name: vdslPerfCurr15MinTimeElapsed
vdslPerfCurr15MinTimeElapsed.description: Total elapsed seconds in this interval.

vdslPerfCurr15MinLofs.name: vdslPerfCurr15MinLofs
vdslPerfCurr15MinLofs.description: Count of seconds during this interval that there was Loss of Framing.

vdslPerfCurr15MinLoss.name: vdslPerfCurr15MinLoss
vdslPerfCurr15MinLoss.description: Count of seconds during this interval that there was Loss of Signal.

vdslPerfCurr15MinLprs.name: vdslPerfCurr15MinLprs
vdslPerfCurr15MinLprs.description: Count of seconds during this interval that there was Loss of Power.

vdslPerfCurr15MinESs.name: vdslPerfCurr15MinESs
vdslPerfCurr15MinESs.description: Count of Errored Seconds during this interval. An Errored Second is a one-second interval containing one or more crc anomalies, or one or more los defects.

vdslPerfCurr15MinInits.name: vdslPerfCurr15MinInits
vdslPerfCurr15MinInits.description: Count of the line initialization attempts during this interval. This count includes both successful and failed attempts.

vdslPerfIntervalTable.name: vdslPerfIntervalTable
vdslPerfIntervalTable.description: This table provides one row for each Vtu performance data collection interval. VDSL physical interfaces are those ifEntries where ifType is equal to vdsl(97).

vdslIntervalNumber.name: vdslIntervalNumber
vdslIntervalNumber.description: Performance Data Interval number 1 is the the most recent previous interval; interval 96 is 24 hours ago. Intervals 2..96 are optional.

vdslIntervalLofs.name: vdslIntervalLofs
vdslIntervalLofs.description: Count of seconds in the interval when there was Loss of Framing.

vdslIntervalLoss.name: vdslIntervalLoss
vdslIntervalLoss.description: Count of seconds in the interval when there was Loss of Signal.

vdslIntervalLprs.name: vdslIntervalLprs
vdslIntervalLprs.description: Count of seconds in the interval when there was Loss of Power.

vdslIntervalESs.name: vdslIntervalESs
vdslIntervalESs.description: Count of Errored Seconds in the interval. An Errored Second is a one-second interval containing one or more crc anomalies, or one or more los defects.

vdslIntervalInits.name: vdslIntervalInits
vdslIntervalInits.description: Count of the line initialization attempts during this interval. This count includes both successful and failed attempts.

vdslChanPerfDataTable.name: vdslChanPerfDataTable
vdslChanPerfDataTable.description: This table provides one row for each Vtu channel. VDSL channel interfaces are those ifEntries where ifType is equal to interleave(124) or fast(125).

vdslChanPerfValidIntervals.name: vdslChanPerfValidIntervals
vdslChanPerfValidIntervals.description: Valid Intervals per xxxValidInterval definition found in HC-PerfHist-TC-MIB.

vdslChanPerfInvalidIntervals.name: vdslChanPerfInvalidIntervals
vdslChanPerfInvalidIntervals.description: Invalid Intervals per xxxInvalidInterval definition found in HC-PerfHist-TC-MIB.

vdslChanCorrectedOctets.name: vdslChanCorrectedOctets
vdslChanCorrectedOctets.description: Count of corrected octets since the unit was last reset.

vdslChanUncorrectBlks.name: vdslChanUncorrectBlks
vdslChanUncorrectBlks.description: Count of uncorrected blocks since the unit was last reset.

vdslChanPerfCurr15MinTimeElapsed.name: vdslChanPerfCurr15MinTimeElapsed
vdslChanPerfCurr15MinTimeElapsed.description: Total elapsed seconds in this interval.

vdslChanPerfCurr15MinCorrectedOctets.name: vdslChanPerfCurr15MinCorrectedOctets
vdslChanPerfCurr15MinCorrectedOctets.description: Count of corrected octets in this interval.

vdslChanPerfCurr15MinUncorrectBlks.name: vdslChanPerfCurr15MinUncorrectBlks
vdslChanPerfCurr15MinUncorrectBlks.description: Count of uncorrected blocks in this interval.

vdslChanIntervalTable.name: vdslChanIntervalTable
vdslChanIntervalTable.description: This table provides one row for each Vtu channel data collection interval. VDSL channel interfaces are those ifEntries where ifType is equal to interleave(124) or fast(125).

vdslChanIntervalNumber.name: vdslChanIntervalNumber
vdslChanIntervalNumber.description: Performance Data Interval number 1 is the the most recent previous interval; interval 96 is 24 hours ago. Intervals 2..96 are optional.

vdslChanIntervalCorrectedOctets.name: vdslChanIntervalCorrectedOctets
vdslChanIntervalCorrectedOctets.description: Count of corrected octets in this interval.

vdslChanIntervalUncorrectBlks.name: vdslChanIntervalUncorrectBlks
vdslChanIntervalUncorrectBlks.description: Count of uncorrected blocks in this interval.

vdslLineConfProfileTable.name: vdslLineConfProfileTable
vdslLineConfProfileTable.description: This table contains information on the VDSL line configuration. One entry in this table reflects a profile defined by a manager which can be used to configure the VDSL line.

vdslLineConfProfileEntry.name: vdslLineConfProfileEntry
vdslLineConfProfileEntry.description: Each entry consists of a list of parameters that represents the configuration of a VDSL modem. A default profile will always exist. This profile's name will be set to `DEFVAL' and its parameters will be set to vendor specific values, unless otherwise specified in this document.

vdslLineConfProfileName.name: vdslLineConfProfileName
vdslLineConfProfileName.description: This object is used by the line configuration table in order to identify a row in that table. The system will always provide a default profile whose name is `DEFVAL'.

vdslLineConfTargetSnrMgn.name: vdslLineConfTargetSnrMgn
vdslLineConfTargetSnrMgn.description: Configured Target Signal/Noise Margin. This is the Noise Margin the modem must achieve with a BER of 10-7 or better to successfully complete initialization.

vdslLineConfTxSpeed.name: vdslLineConfTxSpeed
vdslLineConfTxSpeed.description: Transmit speed for this modem. The corresponding modem on the other end of the VDSL line will have an equal vdslLineConfRxSpeed value.

vdslLineConfRxSpeed.name: vdslLineConfRxSpeed
vdslLineConfRxSpeed.description: Receive speed for this modem. The corresponding modem on the other end of the VDSL line will have an equal vdslLineConfTxSpeed value.

vdslLineConfProfileRowStatus.name: vdslLineConfProfileRowStatus
vdslLineConfProfileRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or modify or delete an existing row in this table. A profile activated by setting this object to `active'. When `active' is set, the system will validate the profile. Before a profile can be deleted or taken out of service, (by setting this object to `destroy' or `outOfService') it must be first unreferenced from all associated lines.

hwVdslLineConfAutoTrain.name: hwVdslLineConfAutoTrain
hwVdslLineConfAutoTrain.description: This object specifies if the modem is allowed to train automatically.

vdslLineMCMConfProfileTable.name: vdslLineMCMConfProfileTable
vdslLineMCMConfProfileTable.description: This table contains information on the VDSL line configuration. One entry in this table reflects a profile defined by a manager which can be used to configure the VDSL line. This table MUST be implemented for multiple carrier VDSL lines. This table MUST NOT be implemented for Single carrier VDSL lines.

vdslLineMCMConfProfileEntry.name: vdslLineMCMConfProfileEntry
vdslLineMCMConfProfileEntry.description: Each entry consists of a list of parameters that represents the configuration of a multiple carrier modulation VDSL modem. A default profile will always exist. This profile's name will be set to `DEFVAL' and its parameters will be set to vendor specific values, unless otherwise specified in this document.

vdslMCMConfProfileTxWindowLength.name: vdslMCMConfProfileTxWindowLength
vdslMCMConfProfileTxWindowLength.description: Specifies the length of the transmit window, counted in samples at the sampling rate corresponding to the negotiated value of N.

vdslMCMConfProfileRowStatus.name: vdslMCMConfProfileRowStatus
vdslMCMConfProfileRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or modify or delete an existing row in this table. A profile activated by setting this object to `active'. When `active' is set, the system will validate the profile. Before a profile can be deleted or taken out of service, (by setting this object to `destroy' or `outOfService') it must be first unreferenced from all associated lines.

vdslLineMCMConfProfileTxBandTable.name: vdslLineMCMConfProfileTxBandTable
vdslLineMCMConfProfileTxBandTable.description: This table contains transmit band descriptor configuration information for a VDSL line. Each entry in this table reflects the configuration for one of possibly many bands with a multiple carrier modulation (MCM) VDSL line. These entries are defined by a manager and can be used to configure the VDSL line. This table MUST be implemented for multiple carrier modulation (MCM) VDSL lines. This table MUST NOT be implemented for single carrier modulation VDSL lines.

vdslLineMCMConfProfileTxBandEntry.name: vdslLineMCMConfProfileTxBandEntry
vdslLineMCMConfProfileTxBandEntry.description: Each entry consists of a transmit band descriptor, which defines the start and stop bands and the power spectral density (PSD) for that band. A default profile will always exist. This profile's name will be set to `DEFVAL' and its parameters will be set to vendor specific values, unless otherwise specified in this document.

vdslMCMConfProfileTxBandNumber.name: vdslMCMConfProfileTxBandNumber
vdslMCMConfProfileTxBandNumber.description: The index for this band descriptor entry.

vdslMCMConfProfileTxBandStart.name: vdslMCMConfProfileTxBandStart
vdslMCMConfProfileTxBandStart.description: Start tone index for this band.

vdslMCMConfProfileTxBandStop.name: vdslMCMConfProfileTxBandStop
vdslMCMConfProfileTxBandStop.description: Stop tone index for this band.

vdslMCMConfProfileTxBandRowStatus.name: vdslMCMConfProfileTxBandRowStatus
vdslMCMConfProfileTxBandRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or modify or delete an existing row in this table. A profile activated by setting this object to `active'. When `active' is set, the system will validate the profile. Before a profile can be deleted or taken out of service, (by setting this object to `destroy' or `outOfService') it must be first unreferenced from all associated lines.

vdslMCMConfProfileTxPSDTone.name: vdslMCMConfProfileTxPSDTone

vdslMCMConfProfileTxPSDPSD.description: Power Spectral Density level in steps of 0.5dB with an offset of -140dbm/Hz.

One entry in this table reflects a profile defined by a manager which can be used to configure the VDSL line. This table MUST be implemented for single carrier modulation (SCM) VDSL lines. This table MUST NOT be implemented for multiple carrier modulation (MCM) VDSL lines.

vdslLineSCMConfProfileEntry.description: Each entry consists of a list of parameters that represents the configuration of a single carrier modulation VDSL modem. A default profile will always exist. This profile's name will be set to `DEFVAL' and its parameters will be set to vendor specific values, unless otherwise specified in this document.

vdslSCMConfProfileFastCodewordSize.name: vdslSCMConfProfileFastCodewordSize
vdslSCMConfProfileFastCodewordSize.description: Specifies the length in octets of the fast codeword. A value of 0 indicates that the single latency transport class is to be utilized.

vdslSCMConfProfileTransmitPSDMask.name: vdslSCMConfProfileTransmitPSDMask
vdslSCMConfProfileTransmitPSDMask.description: The transmit power spectral density mask code.

vdslSCMConfProfileTransmitPSDLevel.name: vdslSCMConfProfileTransmitPSDLevel

vdslSCMConfProfileSymbolRateProfile.name: vdslSCMConfProfileSymbolRateProfile
vdslSCMConfProfileSymbolRateProfile.description: The symbol rate profile calculated as S = SR/BSR, where SR is the required symbol rate in kbaud, BSR = 67.5.

vdslSCMConfProfileCenterFrequency.name: vdslSCMConfProfileCenterFrequency
vdslSCMConfProfileCenterFrequency.description: Specifies the center frequency profile K.

vdslSCMConfProfileRowStatus.name: vdslSCMConfProfileRowStatus
vdslSCMConfProfileRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or modify or delete an existing row in this table. A profile activated by setting this object to `active'. When `active' is set, the system will validate the profile. Before a profile can be deleted or taken out of service, (by setting this object to `destroy' or `outOfService') it must be first unreferenced from all associated lines.

vdslLineAlarmConfProfileTable.name: vdslLineAlarmConfProfileTable
vdslLineAlarmConfProfileTable.description: This table contains information on the VDSL line alarm configuration. One entry in this table reflects a profile defined by a manager which can be used to configure the VDSL line alarm thresholds.

vdslLineAlarmConfProfileEntry.name: vdslLineAlarmConfProfileEntry
vdslLineAlarmConfProfileEntry.description: Each entry consists of a list of parameters that represents the configuration of a VDSL line alarm profile. A default profile will always exist. This profile's name will be set to `DEFVAL' and its parameters will be set to vendor specific values, unless otherwise specified in this document.

vdslLineAlarmConfProfileName.name: vdslLineAlarmConfProfileName
vdslLineAlarmConfProfileName.description: This object is used by the line alarm configuration table in order to identify a row in that table. The system will always provide a default profile whose name is `DEFVAL'.

vdslThresh15MinLofs.name: vdslThresh15MinLofs
vdslThresh15MinLofs.description: This object configures the threshold for the number of loss of frame seconds (lofs) within any given 15-minute performance data collection interval. If the value of loss of frame seconds in a particular 15-minute collection interval reaches/exceeds this value, a vdslPerfLofsThreshNotification notification will be generated. No more than one notification will be sent per interval.

vdslThresh15MinLoss.name: vdslThresh15MinLoss
vdslThresh15MinLoss.description: This object configures the threshold for the number of loss of signal seconds (loss) within any given 15-minute performance data collection interval. If the value of loss of frame seconds in a particular 15-minute collection interval reaches/exceeds this value, a vdslPerfLossThreshNotification notification will be generated. One notification will be sent per interval per endpoint.

vdslThresh15MinLprs.name: vdslThresh15MinLprs
vdslThresh15MinLprs.description: This object configures the threshold for the number of loss of power seconds (lprs) within any given 15-minute performance data collection interval. If the value of loss of frame seconds in a particular 15-minute collection interval reaches/exceeds this value, a vdslPerfLprsThreshNotification notification will be generated. No more than one notification will be sent per interval.

vdslThresh15MinESs.name: vdslThresh15MinESs
vdslThresh15MinESs.description: This object configures the threshold for the number of errored seconds (lofs) within any given 15-minute performance data collection interval. If the value of loss of frame seconds in a particular 15-minute collection interval reaches/exceeds this value, a vdslPerfESsThreshNotification notification will be generated. No more than one notification will be sent per interval.

vdslInitFailureNotificationEnable.name: vdslInitFailureNotificationEnable
vdslInitFailureNotificationEnable.description: This object specifies if a vdslInitFailureNotification notification will be generated if an initialization failure occurs.

vdslLineAlarmConfProfileRowStatus.name: vdslLineAlarmConfProfileRowStatus
vdslLineAlarmConfProfileRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or modify or delete an existing row in this table. A profile activated by setting this object to `active'. When `active' is set, the system will validate the profile. Before a profile can be deleted or taken out of service, (by setting this object to `destroy' or `outOfService') it must be first unreferenced from all associated lines.

hwVdslEtherStatsTable.name: hwVdslEtherStatsTable
hwVdslEtherStatsTable.description: This table provides one row for each Vtu. Each row contains the ehternet statistic Parameters table for that Vtu.This table is Ether state for VDSL table.

hwVdslEtherStatsEntry.name: hwVdslEtherStatsEntry
hwVdslEtherStatsEntry.description: An entry in the hwVdslEtherStatsTable. This table defines and collects the statistical data of Ether.

hwVdslEtherStatsAlignmentErrors.name: hwVdslEtherStatsAlignmentErrors
hwVdslEtherStatsAlignmentErrors.description: The total number of frames received with alignment errors (an odd number of nibbles).

hwVdslEtherStatsSingleCollisionFrames.name: hwVdslEtherStatsSingleCollisionFrames
hwVdslEtherStatsSingleCollisionFrames.description: A count of successfully transmitted frames for which transmission was inhibited by exactly one collision.

hwVdslEtherStatsMultipleCollisionFrames.name: hwVdslEtherStatsMultipleCollisionFrames
hwVdslEtherStatsMultipleCollisionFrames.description: A count of successfully transmitted frames for which transmission was inhibited by more than one collision.

hwVdslEtherStatsDeferredTransmissions.name: hwVdslEtherStatsDeferredTransmissions
hwVdslEtherStatsDeferredTransmissions.description: A count of frames for which the first transmission attempt was delayed because the Ethernet media was busy.

hwVdslEtherStatsLateCollisionFrames.name: hwVdslEtherStatsLateCollisionFrames
hwVdslEtherStatsLateCollisionFrames.description: The total number of times that a collision was detected on a particular interface later than 512 bit-times into the transmission of a packet.

hwVdslEtherStatsExcessiveCollisionFrames.name: hwVdslEtherStatsExcessiveCollisionFrames
hwVdslEtherStatsExcessiveCollisionFrames.description: A count of frames for which transmission failed due to excessive collisions.

hwVdslEtherStatsReceiveErrors.name: hwVdslEtherStatsReceiveErrors
hwVdslEtherStatsReceiveErrors.description: The total number of frames received with less than 64 bytes.

hwVdslEtherStatsCarrierErrors.name: hwVdslEtherStatsCarrierErrors
hwVdslEtherStatsCarrierErrors.description: The total number of times that the carrier sense condition was lost or never asserted when attempting to transmit a frame on a particular interface.

hwVdslEtherStatsTooLongErrors.name: hwVdslEtherStatsTooLongErrors
hwVdslEtherStatsTooLongErrors.description: The total number of frames received with more than maximum length.

hwVdslEtherStatsSequenceErrors.name: hwVdslEtherStatsSequenceErrors
hwVdslEtherStatsSequenceErrors.description: The total number of frames received that had a bad Frame Check Sequence (FCS).

hwVdslEtherStatsTransmitOctets.name: hwVdslEtherStatsTransmitOctets
hwVdslEtherStatsTransmitOctets.description: A count of data and padding octets of frames that are successfully transmitted.

hwVdslEtherStatsReceiveOctets.name: hwVdslEtherStatsReceiveOctets
hwVdslEtherStatsReceiveOctets.description: A count of data and padding octets of frames that are successfully received.

hwVdslEtherStatsReceiveBroadcastFrames.name: hwVdslEtherStatsReceiveBroadcastFrames
hwVdslEtherStatsReceiveBroadcastFrames.description: A count of frames that are successfully received and are directed to the broadcast group address.

hwVdslEtherStatsReceivePauseFrames.name: hwVdslEtherStatsReceivePauseFrames
hwVdslEtherStatsReceivePauseFrames.description: The total number of PAUSE packets received.

hwVdslEtherStatsTransmitPauseFrames.name: hwVdslEtherStatsTransmitPauseFrames
hwVdslEtherStatsTransmitPauseFrames.description: The total number of PAUSE packets transmitted.

hwVdslEtherStatsTransmitFrames.name: hwVdslEtherStatsTransmitFrames
hwVdslEtherStatsTransmitFrames.description: The total number of valid data frames that have been transferred over the transmit channel.

hwVdslEtherStatsReceiveFrames.name: hwVdslEtherStatsReceiveFrames
hwVdslEtherStatsReceiveFrames.description: The total number of valid data frames that have been transferred over the receive channel.

vdslPerfLofsThreshNotification.name: vdslPerfLofsThreshNotification
vdslPerfLofsThreshNotification.description: Loss of Framing 15-minute interval threshold reached.

vdslPerfLossThreshNotification.name: vdslPerfLossThreshNotification
vdslPerfLossThreshNotification.description: Loss of Signal 15-minute interval threshold reached.

vdslPerfLprsThreshNotification.name: vdslPerfLprsThreshNotification
vdslPerfLprsThreshNotification.description: Loss of Power 15-minute interval threshold reached.

vdslInitFailureNotification.name: vdslInitFailureNotification
vdslInitFailureNotification.description: Vtu initialization failed. See vdslCurrStatus for potential reasons.

vdslLineMibCompliance.name: vdslLineMibCompliance
vdslLineMibCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMP entities which manage VDSL interfaces.
